Centralized Container Logging with the EFK Stack
Objectives
Design and deploy a production-grade EFK (Elasticsearch, Fluentd, Kibana) logging pipeline using Docker Compose
Configure Fluentd to collect, parse, and route logs from multiple containerized applications into Elasticsearch
Implement log-based alerting by querying Elasticsearch and triggering threshold-driven notifications
Prerequisites
Comfort with Linux command-line operations including file editing, process management, and network inspection
Familiarity with YAML syntax and basic Docker concepts such as images, containers, and networks
Understanding of structured logging concepts including log levels, JSON formatting, and index-based storage
Lab Environment
You will work on a dedicated AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance provided by Al Nafi. The instance has a base Ubuntu installation; you will install all required tools in Task 1.

